GAUTENG ANC chairman Paul Mashatile may add his name to the growing list of candidates who want to succeed Jacob Zuma as ANC president in December.City Press reported yesterday that Mashatile said he was ready to be nominated for any position in the top six, even that of president. If Mashatile stands for president, he will become the seventh candidate to throw his name into the hat. Mashatile told the newspaper if the ANC wanted him to stand, he wouldn&rsquo;t say no because he needed to listen to the will of the people. He is among the ANC leaders who have been campaigning for deputy president Cyril Ramaphosa to take over from Zuma.